30:11.798 --> 30:16.798
♪ Git along, little doggie,
git along, git along ♪

30:16.881 --> 30:21.172
♪ Git along, little doggie,
git along ♪

30:21.255 --> 30:26.297
♪ Git along, little doggie,
git along, git along  ♪

30:26.381 --> 30:29.130
♪ Git along, little doggie  ♪

30:29.214 --> 30:32.005
-♪ Git along ♪
-(ticking continuing)

30:32.089 --> 30:36.381
♪ I'm heading for the last... ♪

30:36.464 --> 30:40.172
(ticking echoing)

30:44.214 --> 30:46.506
-Man: Nobody fucking move!
-(gasps, murmurs)

30:46.589 --> 30:47.964
This device is connected
to my heart,

30:48.047 --> 30:50.172
so if it stops beating,
you're all fucking dead!

30:50.255 --> 30:52.798
(ticking continuing)

30:52.881 --> 30:54.923
Senator Joseph Keene, Jr.--

30:55.005 --> 30:57.047
you are a race traitor

30:57.130 --> 30:59.756
and declared open war
on the Seventh Kavalry.

30:59.839 --> 31:03.130
Surrender yourself
or everyone dies!

31:03.214 --> 31:05.339
Hey! What did I fucking say?

31:05.422 --> 31:07.631
Hey. Just take it easy.

31:08.464 --> 31:10.255
I'll do whatever you want.

31:12.297 --> 31:13.881
Okay? Take it easy.

31:14.714 --> 31:16.297
Here I am.

31:16.381 --> 31:18.547
(ticking echoing)

31:23.130 --> 31:24.798
-Do not attempt to follow--
-(gunshot)

31:24.881 --> 31:26.756
(crowd gasping, screaming)

31:26.839 --> 31:29.631
(crowd murmuring)

31:29.714 --> 31:33.881
(bomb beeping)

31:33.964 --> 31:36.589
-Run!
-(panicked shouting,
screaming)

31:36.673 --> 31:39.005
Blake: Go! Go! Go! Go!

31:39.089 --> 31:42.089
(beeping quickens)

31:49.422 --> 31:51.589
(bomb beeping quickly)

31:52.798 --> 31:54.673
(beeping echoing)

31:54.756 --> 31:56.756
(grunting)

31:59.964 --> 32:01.714
(exploding)

32:01.798 --> 32:03.339
(grunts)

32:18.964 --> 32:23.172
♪ Get up in the morning,
slaving for bread, sir  ♪

32:23.255 --> 32:27.756
(playing on phonograph):
♪ So that every mouth
can be fed ♪

32:27.839 --> 32:34.339
♪ Poor me Israelites, ah ♪

32:37.673 --> 32:41.214
♪ Get up in the morning,
slaving for bread, sir ♪

32:41.297 --> 32:44.255
♪ So that every mouth
can be fed ♪

32:44.339 --> 32:50.464
♪ Poor me Israelites ♪

32:50.547 --> 32:54.214
♪ My wife and my kids,
they packed up and leave me ♪

32:54.297 --> 32:57.589
♪ Darling, she said,
I was yours to be seen ♪

32:57.673 --> 33:02.255
♪ Poor me Israelites ♪

33:03.547 --> 33:06.714
♪ Shirt them a-tear up,
trousers is gone ♪

33:06.798 --> 33:10.422
♪ I don't want to end up
like Bonnie and Clyde ♪

33:10.506 --> 33:15.047
♪ Poor me Israelites ♪

33:16.673 --> 33:19.631
♪ After a storm
there must be a calm ♪

33:19.714 --> 33:23.172
♪ They catch me in the farm,
you sound your alarm ♪

33:23.255 --> 33:27.673
♪ Poor me Israelites ♪

33:27.756 --> 33:30.255
♪ Eee ♪

33:41.881 --> 33:45.964
♪ I said I get up
in the morning
slaving for bread, sir ♪

33:46.047 --> 33:49.047
♪ So that every mouth
can be fed ♪

33:49.130 --> 33:54.089
♪ Poor me Israelites... ♪

33:56.756 --> 34:00.047
This... is going to be the one.

34:02.255 --> 34:04.964
I feel it in my bones.

34:05.047 --> 34:07.381
I never doubted you, Master.

34:07.464 --> 34:08.673
That, Mr. Philips,

34:08.756 --> 34:12.130
is because you are
incapable of doubt.

34:15.547 --> 34:18.631
Nevertheless, I appreciate
the sentiment.

34:21.005 --> 34:22.506
Oh.

34:23.631 --> 34:25.005
Master:
Right.

34:29.089 --> 34:32.214
Are you ready to venture
into the great beyond?

34:32.297 --> 34:35.172
Oh. Yes, I am, sir.

34:38.297 --> 34:40.297
(oxygen hissing)

34:45.130 --> 34:47.839
(breathing deeply)

35:01.339 --> 35:04.339
(footsteps approaching)

35:11.464 --> 35:13.547
(sighs)

35:15.881 --> 35:17.714
(oxygen hissing)

35:18.714 --> 35:22.047
(sighs)
Damn it.

35:24.923 --> 35:26.464
(growling)

35:26.547 --> 35:29.422
Damn it. Damn it!

35:29.506 --> 35:32.047
Shit! Fuck! Shit!

35:32.130 --> 35:35.756
Shit and shit and fuck!

35:35.839 --> 35:38.130
Motherfucking shit!

35:38.214 --> 35:42.339
Fucking damn it!
And motherfucking shit!

35:42.422 --> 35:46.297
(shouts, grunts)

35:46.381 --> 35:48.422
What went wrong, Master?

35:51.089 --> 35:53.881
I think we're going to need
a thicker skin.

36:46.047 --> 36:48.589
(buffalo bellowing)

37:03.005 --> 37:05.798
(gunshot echoing)

37:15.798 --> 37:17.756
(door slams open)

37:19.964 --> 37:23.714
Both:
♪ For he's a jolly good fellow,
for he's a jolly-- ♪

37:23.798 --> 37:25.631
(shatters)

37:29.422 --> 37:32.631
(footsteps echoing)

37:43.172 --> 37:47.673
(clears throat)
I'm so sorry
to disturb you, Master.

37:48.839 --> 37:50.506
But there's a letter.

37:51.923 --> 37:53.506
From the game warden.

37:55.547 --> 37:57.005
Read it to me.

37:58.589 --> 38:02.464
Let's see what our adversary
has to say for himself.

38:07.130 --> 38:11.631
-"Dear Mas--"
-Oh, dispense with the flowery
pleasantries and get to it.

38:11.714 --> 38:15.255
"I beg your pardon, sir,
but when you first arrived here,

38:15.339 --> 38:18.464
"we agreed upon
the terms of your captivity.

38:18.547 --> 38:20.089
"Your recent behavior suggests

38:20.172 --> 38:22.214
an intention to violate
those terms."

38:22.297 --> 38:24.214
-Hmm.
-"As such,

38:24.297 --> 38:25.798
"if this behavior continues,

38:25.881 --> 38:28.881
you will face
grave consequences."

38:32.339 --> 38:34.297
He's underscored
"consequences."

38:34.381 --> 38:36.631
-Mm.
-"Know this--

38:36.714 --> 38:39.631
"The next shot I fire, sir,
will not be at your feet.

38:39.714 --> 38:42.964
"Please consider this
your first and only warning.

38:43.047 --> 38:46.130
"Thank you again for
the delicious tomatoes.

38:46.214 --> 38:49.547
Your humble servant,
The Game Warden."

38:52.381 --> 38:54.798
To the typewriter,
Crookshanks!

38:59.422 --> 39:03.631
Let's see what this devious
cur is made of, shall we?

39:03.714 --> 39:06.381
-Oh, yes, we shall, Master!
-Mm.

39:07.172 --> 39:08.964
Most Honorable Game Warden.

39:09.047 --> 39:11.130
-(typewriter clacking)
-I beg your pardon, sir,

39:11.214 --> 39:14.422
but you seem to suspect me
of criminal activities

39:14.506 --> 39:18.297
as if I were a dastardly
forest brigand.

39:18.381 --> 39:23.589
Or worse, some sort of
republic serial villain.

39:24.297 --> 39:25.297
I am neither, sir,

39:25.381 --> 39:29.756
And I assure you
that my activities

39:29.839 --> 39:34.422
are purely recreational
in nature.

39:35.297 --> 39:38.005
Furthermore,
I would never imagine

39:38.089 --> 39:41.172
to transgress the terms
upon which we agreed.

39:42.005 --> 39:46.714
I am available, at your
leisure and by your grace,

39:46.798 --> 39:50.422
to discuss this matter further
should you wish to repeat

39:50.506 --> 39:53.422
your ridiculous accusations
in person.

39:55.130 --> 39:57.756
That said, I'm pleased
you enjoyed the tomatoes.

39:57.839 --> 40:02.839
All the best wishes
and encouragement,

40:04.130 --> 40:06.839
Adrian Veidt.

40:08.464 --> 40:10.798
What do you think,
Ms. Crookshanks?

40:11.923 --> 40:15.089
Oh, this will have him quaking
in his boots, Master!

40:16.381 --> 40:18.005
I'll have it sent right away.

40:19.464 --> 40:21.631
Have Mr. Philips
restring my bow

40:21.714 --> 40:23.839
and saddle up Bucephalus.

40:24.381 --> 40:26.714
I hunt again at midnight!

40:55.339 --> 40:57.381
(thundering)

40:57.464 --> 40:59.756
Senator Keene:
I am not the hero here.

40:59.839 --> 41:03.464
I'm only standing here
talking to y'all right now

41:03.547 --> 41:07.756
because of the swift
and fearless actions
of law enforcement.

41:07.839 --> 41:10.839
They are the heroes.
They kept me safe.

41:10.923 --> 41:13.798
And I'll be damned
if I won't keep fighting
to do the same for them.

41:13.881 --> 41:15.172
Reporter:
Senator Keene--

41:15.255 --> 41:18.005
Why do you think you were
targeted by the Kavalry?

41:18.089 --> 41:20.422
I reckon it's because nothing
scares a terrorist more

41:20.506 --> 41:22.130
than someone
they can't terrify.

41:22.214 --> 41:25.130
Can you comment on
the Russians building
an intrinsic field generator?

41:25.214 --> 41:26.339
Keene:
Guys...

41:26.422 --> 41:28.464
when they swore me in,
I promised to defend us

41:28.547 --> 41:30.964
from all enemies
foreign and domestic.

41:31.047 --> 41:35.130
But I represent the people
of the great state of Oklahoma,

41:35.214 --> 41:37.464
and the Russians
ain't my problem.

41:37.547 --> 41:39.839
The goddamned
Seventh Kavalry is.

41:40.506 --> 41:43.005
Right now, here is
where the war's at.

41:43.089 --> 41:45.589
And I won't be leaving
until it's won.

41:46.297 --> 41:48.422
Good night and God Bless.

41:48.506 --> 41:51.798
(reporters shouting questions)

41:54.798 --> 41:56.839
Well, he's got my vote.

41:56.923 --> 41:59.214
Are you even old
enough to vote?

42:00.714 --> 42:03.756
So, can I get
that autograph now or...?

42:04.964 --> 42:07.297
That was almost
funny, Petey.

42:07.923 --> 42:10.798
-You drink any of that yet?
-No. Why?

42:56.381 --> 42:58.422
How about that coffee now?

43:01.798 --> 43:03.589
Where's it go?

43:04.339 --> 43:07.130
(sighs)
Just outside the fence.

43:07.214 --> 43:09.464
Gotta be 300 meters long.

43:09.547 --> 43:12.255
Must've used some kind've drill
to get it done that fast.

43:12.339 --> 43:14.673
Don't rule out
extremist gophers.

43:19.589 --> 43:21.130
How are your children?

43:22.422 --> 43:23.673
Safe.

43:24.881 --> 43:26.923
(sighs)
I thought he was bluffing.

43:27.673 --> 43:29.923
Those fuckers always say
the device is rigged
to their hearts,

43:30.005 --> 43:32.297
and none of them actually
take the time to do it.

43:33.631 --> 43:35.673
You saved us. Thanks.

43:36.297 --> 43:37.923
Crawford jumped
on the grenade.

43:38.005 --> 43:41.005
I just gave him
a little push.

43:42.381 --> 43:44.255
Yeah, well...
(chuckles)

43:44.339 --> 43:46.547
I sure as shit can't
exhume him now.

43:47.464 --> 43:48.881
That's not funny.

43:49.673 --> 43:51.673
Sorry. I wasn't joking.

43:51.756 --> 43:53.964
You guys just scheduled
this funeral so fast.

43:54.047 --> 43:55.339
Kinda weird considering

43:55.422 --> 43:57.756
it's an active murder
investigation by the way,

43:57.839 --> 43:59.130
but, uh...

43:59.214 --> 44:01.547
we were literally gonna
dig him up tomorrow.

44:01.631 --> 44:03.589
Discretely, of course.

44:04.714 --> 44:06.005
Why?

44:08.673 --> 44:11.130
Your chief was murdered
by the Seventh Kavalry.

44:11.214 --> 44:13.756
I get it,
there's a history.

44:13.839 --> 44:15.130
But...

44:15.214 --> 44:18.172
you still have to consider
other possibilities, right?

44:18.714 --> 44:20.547
For instance, I was
at the crime scene earlier,

44:20.631 --> 44:22.339
and you know what I saw?
Tire tracks,

44:22.422 --> 44:24.255
right at the base
of the tree.

44:25.714 --> 44:26.964
What kind of vehicle?

44:27.047 --> 44:29.089
I'm sorry. Did I say vehicle?
No, no, no.

44:29.172 --> 44:31.881
No, um, it was a wheelchair.

44:34.506 --> 44:36.255
And I get how
you guys missed it.

44:36.339 --> 44:39.381
You know, he was your chief,
he was your friend.

44:39.464 --> 44:41.089
It's hard to do
your job well

44:41.172 --> 44:42.964
when you're that close
to someone.

44:43.047 --> 44:44.881
That's why I'm here.

44:44.964 --> 44:46.172
Hey, did you know
that he had

44:46.255 --> 44:48.839
a secret compartment
in his closet?

44:48.923 --> 44:51.506
-What?
-Yeah, I was over there
talking to his wife,

44:51.589 --> 44:54.089
and while I was there
I found this secret
fucking compartment.

44:54.172 --> 44:55.673
Isn't that insane?

44:55.756 --> 44:57.297
Why were you looking
in his closet?

44:57.381 --> 45:00.172
Oh. Well, when my dad
was murdered,

45:00.255 --> 45:03.506
they found a secret
compartment in his closet.

45:03.589 --> 45:05.047
So, you know...

45:05.923 --> 45:07.214
I always check.

45:07.881 --> 45:10.047
Once in a while, it pans out.

45:13.673 --> 45:15.547
What was in it?

45:17.756 --> 45:20.464
You tell me.
What was in it?

45:21.631 --> 45:23.756
How the fuck
should I know?

45:23.839 --> 45:25.047
Well...

45:25.130 --> 45:27.506
his wife told me
that you were the only person

45:27.589 --> 45:29.339
in that bedroom
since he died.

45:30.422 --> 45:33.923
And frankly, Angela...
(chuckles)

45:34.589 --> 45:37.464
you just don't strike me
as the fainting type.

45:42.214 --> 45:44.631
Okay, I'll tell you.

45:45.464 --> 45:48.297
It was a bust,
just a big, naked bust.

45:48.381 --> 45:50.506
That's it.
However...

45:51.255 --> 45:52.756
I think there was
something on that bust.

45:52.839 --> 45:55.214
I don't know.
Maybe your pal Judd asked you

45:55.297 --> 45:56.923
to get rid of it
if something ever happened,

45:57.005 --> 45:59.255
or, you know, maybe the two
of you were having an affair,

45:59.339 --> 46:02.881
which makes no sense because
your husband's fucking hot.

46:03.756 --> 46:06.798
But whatever it is,
this much I know--

46:09.005 --> 46:10.923
Men who end up
hanging from trees

46:11.005 --> 46:13.422
with secret compartments
in their closets

46:13.506 --> 46:16.005
tend to think of themselves
as good guys.

46:17.172 --> 46:21.839
And those who protect them
think they're good guys too.

46:22.756 --> 46:25.714
But here's the thing
about me, "Sister Night"...

46:28.172 --> 46:30.506
I eat good guys for breakfast.

46:37.172 --> 46:38.631
Ooh!

47:06.339 --> 47:08.839
Blake:
And so, it's been a long day
at the pearly gates.

47:08.923 --> 47:11.297
All the heroes have
gone to Hell.

47:11.381 --> 47:15.047
His work done,
God's packing up to go home.

47:15.130 --> 47:17.506
And then he notices
someone waiting.

47:18.964 --> 47:22.214
But it's not a hero.
It's just a woman.

47:22.297 --> 47:25.005
"Where did you come from?"
asks God.

47:25.089 --> 47:28.631
"Oh, I was standing
behind those other guys
the whole time.

47:29.547 --> 47:31.464
You just didn't see me."

47:34.547 --> 47:37.589
"Did I give you a talent?"
God asks.

47:38.673 --> 47:40.714
-"Nope."
-(knocking)

47:40.798 --> 47:43.214
"None to speak of,"
says the woman.

47:45.714 --> 47:48.297
God gives her a good long look.

47:52.047 --> 47:57.172
"I'm so sorry.
I'm embarrassed.

47:57.255 --> 48:01.923
"Seriously, this almost
never happens, but...

48:03.047 --> 48:05.130
I don't know who you are."

48:06.297 --> 48:11.005
And the woman looks at God
and she quietly says:

48:16.005 --> 48:19.297
"I'm the little girl who threw
the brick in the air."

48:23.172 --> 48:27.047
Then a sound from above,
something falling.

48:27.130 --> 48:28.923
The brick.

48:29.005 --> 48:33.547
God looks up, but it's too late.
He never saw it coming.

48:33.631 --> 48:37.464
It hits him so hard,
his brains shoot out his nose.

48:38.506 --> 48:41.589
Game over.
He's dead.

48:43.589 --> 48:46.464
And where does God go
when he dies?

48:47.089 --> 48:49.047
He goes to Hell.

48:50.923 --> 48:52.798
Roll on snare drum.

48:53.756 --> 48:55.214
Curtains.

48:57.923 --> 49:00.089
Good joke.

49:00.172 --> 49:02.631
Automated Voice:
Sorry. Your time is almost up.

49:02.714 --> 49:06.381
You have 55 seconds to
complete your transmission.

49:09.047 --> 49:10.589
(sighs)

49:10.673 --> 49:13.589
I don't know why I keep coming
to these stupid phone booths

49:13.673 --> 49:15.673
and telling you jokes.

49:17.798 --> 49:20.464
It's not like you ever had
a sense of humor.

49:23.297 --> 49:26.172
You're never gonna hear
this anyway probably.

49:27.673 --> 49:30.589
but sometimes it's,
you know, it's nice to...

49:34.005 --> 49:36.172
sometimes it's nice to pretend.

49:38.547 --> 49:41.547
The assholes down here
still think you give a shit.

49:43.255 --> 49:46.172
even though you've been on
another fucking planet for--

49:46.255 --> 49:48.506
for 30 years.

49:54.464 --> 49:56.089
(sighs)

49:58.339 --> 50:01.130
But we're not really worth
giving a shit about anyway,
are we?

50:01.214 --> 50:02.673
Automated Voice:
Recording complete.

50:02.756 --> 50:05.339
Thank you for being a platinum
user of the Blue Booth Network.

50:05.422 --> 50:09.089
Your message will reach Mars
in approximately 40 seconds.

50:09.172 --> 50:12.589
Good night, and thank you for
contacting Doctor Manhattan.

50:12.673 --> 50:14.214
Good night, Jon.

50:23.089 --> 50:26.089
(warbling)

50:47.756 --> 50:50.422
(low rumbling)

50:52.464 --> 50:57.089
-(shattering)
-(car alarms blaring)

51:02.631 --> 51:04.255
What the--?

51:30.547 --> 51:33.673
(laughing)

53:56.631 --> 53:57.422
(DOORBELL RINGS)

53:57.506 --> 53:59.714
-LADY TRIEU: Hi.
-You're Lady Trieu.

53:59.964 --> 54:01.089
I sure am.

54:01.339 --> 54:03.255
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

54:03.631 --> 54:05.172
I'm here to offer you legacy.

54:07.381 --> 54:08.756
Legacy as in blood.

54:09.964 --> 54:11.339
MAN: What is that?

54:13.130 --> 54:15.798
LADY TRIEU: The first wonder
of the new world.

54:16.798 --> 54:17.923
LOOKING GLASS:
What can I do you for?

54:18.130 --> 54:19.422
He hid it in his closet.

54:19.923 --> 54:22.547
LOOKING GLASS: Looks like
we have ourselves a reckoning.

54:23.881 --> 54:25.881
-Are we loaded, Mr. Phillips?
-Yes, sir.

54:25.964 --> 54:27.839
On my mark, Ms. Crookshanks.

54:28.881 --> 54:31.297
Three, two, one...

54:31.714 --> 54:32.839
Away!

54:34.839 --> 54:36.172
Phenomenal!

54:37.339 --> 54:39.172
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
